abstract: >-
  Moonlit Showrunner is an AI-assisted short-film prototyping pipeline built
  with Python and Streamlit. Starting from a story premise, the system generates
  a structured story package, character profiles, a script, storyboard, visual
  prompts, continuity notes, reusable character reference cards, generated scene
  images, a visual animatic MP4, and optional Sora video clips assembled into a
  final video output. Version 0.7.3 focuses on the kitten-centered version of
  the project, following Milo, a small kitten who loses his first tooth and
  discovers a moonlit fairy archive. This release explores character continuity,
  creative workflow control, moderation-aware Sora prompt sanitization, and
  human-in-the-loop AI-assisted production.
